OL,3,CHouseholds set for lower energy bills
OL,4,Camid price cap shake-up
OL,6,FNed Hammond, deputy director of
OL,7,Fcustomer policy at Energy UK, which
OL,8,Frepresents firms, said: "While the
OL,9,Fsaving will be #150 for the average
OL,10,Fhousehold, it is important to note
OL,11,Fthat the discount is applied to the
OL,12,Funit rate. Therefore, households will
OL,13,Fexperience significantly different
OL,14,Fsavings depending on their energy
OL,15,Fconsumption, some much higher and
OL,16,Fothers substantially lower than #150.
