OL,3,CHouseholds set for lower energy bills
OL,4,Camid price cap shake-up
OL,6,F"In addition, other moving parts, such
OL,7,Fas network charges and wholesale
OL,8,Fcosts, mean energy bills will not
OL,9,Fnecessarily fall in line with the
OL,10,Fsaving provided. Indeed, the price cap
OL,11,Fis projected to drop by around #115
OL,12,Ffrom 1 April."
OL,14,FWhich? energy editor Emily Seymour
OL,15,Fsaid: "Households can expect a
OL,16,Fsignificant cut to their energy bills
OL,17,Fin April, which will come as a relief
OL,18,Fto millions of people struggling with
OL,19,Fcost-of-living pressures.
